). Female unknown. Body length. ♂ : 2.92± 0.16 mm (n=12). Robust, sturdy, uniformly reddish brown, covered with double pubescence.

Pronotum (
Figure 6m
). Longer than wide, disc convex. Sides subparallel from base to the apical third, then converging markedly inward toward apical margin anteriorly. Densely punctuated, space between points smaller than the diameters of points. Covered with double pubescence, short blond hairs borne from the punctation and pulverulent interspersed hairs. Base bi-sinuated with a light fringe of golden pubescence anterior to the scutellum.
